11#ifndef COMMON_VIDEO_H265_H265_SPS_PARSER_H_
12#define COMMON_VIDEO_H265_H265_SPS_PARSER_H_
13
14#include "absl/types/optional.h"
15
16namespace rtc {
17class BitBuffer;
18}
19
20namespace webrtc {
21
22// A class for parsing out sequence parameter set (SPS) data from an H265 NALU.
23class H265SpsParser {
24 public:
25 // The parsed state of the SPS. Only some select values are stored.
26 // Add more as they are actually needed.
27 struct SpsState {
28 SpsState();
29
30 uint32_t width = 0;
31 uint32_t height = 0;
32 uint32_t delta_pic_order_always_zero_flag = 0;
33 uint32_t separate_colour_plane_flag = 0;
34 uint32_t frame_mbs_only_flag = 0;
35 uint32_t log2_max_frame_num_minus4 = 0;
36 uint32_t log2_max_pic_order_cnt_lsb_minus4 = 0;
37 uint32_t pic_order_cnt_type = 0;
38 uint32_t max_num_ref_frames = 0;
39 uint32_t vui_params_present = 0;
40 uint32_t id = 0;
41 uint32_t vps_id = 0;
42 };
43
44 // Unpack RBSP and parse SPS state from the supplied buffer.
45 static absl::optional<SpsState> ParseSps(const uint8_t* data, size_t length);
46
47 protected:
48 // Parse the SPS state, up till the VUI part, for a bit buffer where RBSP
49 // decoding has already been performed.
50 static absl::optional<SpsState> ParseSpsUpToVui(rtc::BitBuffer* buffer);
51};
52
53} // namespace webrtc
54#endif // COMMON_VIDEO_H265_H265_SPS_PARSER_H_
